100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 7, 1925, the international community was abuzz as the League of Nations continued to grapple with disarmament discussions, highlighting tensions in Europe. In the United States, the oil industry faced scrutiny following a Senate investigation into the practices of major companies. Meanwhile, in Asia, Japan's growing military influence raised concerns among neighboring nations, reflecting the shifting dynamics in the region.
